properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 27 at 12:01PM PST until January 28 at 3:00AM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Wind Advisory, northeast winds 20 to 30 mph with
gusts up to 50 mph expected. For the High Wind Watch, northeast
winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 65 mph possible.

* WHERE...Santa Barbara County Mountains.

* WHEN...For the Wind Advisory, until 3 AM PST Tuesday. For the
High Wind Watch, from Tuesday evening through Wednesday
evening.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds could blow down large objects such as
trees and power lines. Power outages are possible. Travel
could be difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Highways 101 and 154 will be affected with
the strongest winds in the Montecito Hills, San Marcos Pass, and
Gaviota/Refugio areas.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.
